caption: Literally the best :) go-to spot
Ordered online with them and one hour later they cancelled my order. Very disrespectful.
Great happy hour deals!! Happy hour is also from 11am - 7pm if I'm not mistaken so plenty of time to come here and get your drink on! Sitting on the patio is great, especially at night.
It should be noted that we’ve only had the pleasure of eating their nachos. But that being said, MY GOD! These are by far our favorites, and we eat them perhaps a bit too often! :)

I have my curated list of favorites - chicken satay, papaya salad, red curry, tom yum soup (with and without the noodles), and the curried rice! All these dishes travel well. The only one in my experience that doesn't, are the steamed dumplings.
Portions could be better. Over priced. There should be a variety of frozen drinks. Etc some coconut based. Pina colada or pain killer frozen drink.
Very nice
Chicken tacos are as authentic as it gets.  Best tacos ive tried in area

My bestie and I came out for a little air. She wanted tacos and said this spot had good ones. The outdoor dining was a plus. I tried the shrimp one which wasn't bad. It's nothing to brag about. They use corn tortillas which I'm not a fan of. I wouldn't return bc of the service. So, we asked the waitress if she cld clean the table (my friend did point out some leftover food on her side) only one side was cleaned. Even after I got up and moved my stuff. She then disappeared inside and never returned. I couldn't get pass that.
This past Saturday I ordered loaded nachos with extra everything this is what I got.

Taqueria Diana is my #1 favorite Mexican restaurant. The shrimp tacos and nachos often reappear in my dreams! The vibe is awesome, they have fun DJ'd events, and the service is always on point. Get some!

Every time I eat here, I remember why this is the best taqueria out there. The Nachos are amazing! The Tacos are amazing! The Draft cocktails amazing! I’ve ordered takeout many times as well and everything comes exactly how I would get it at the restaurant. I highly recommend!
Nachos are epic and tacos are awesome (plus great tortillas)
Probably the best Mexican food outside of California

Great food. Helpful employees. Legitimate mexican tacos with mexican soda. Very clean place with a variety of hot sauce. I don't have much to complain about. Hipster crowd. No parking. Price is on the higher end.
Music was bomb for Saturday night... great admosfera for tasty tacos and burritos
10/10. V good
Nice place food xoxo
Great tacos...good music...great vibe
Great tasting and unique margs, good food. Really fun decor.
Nice ambience and great tacos.
Best business model for a restaurant ever. Pay up front and you aren't bothered from then on. Fantastic nachos and margaritas. Top shelf.
The menu and service were above my expectations. I absolutely loved the vibes of this restaurant. Awesome place to take the family out for dinner.
T.R.A.S.H...do yourself a favor and go somewhere else
Delicious Food, Fast Service, Decent Pricing. What more could be asked?

This was not my first time here, but every time I come it’s the steak quesadilla. And now everyone is copying me. Melty cheese, steak with just the right amount of seasoning, and a bunch of salsa to choose from. I loves it.

Great tacos, even if they're a little pricey. $1 tortilla baskets make up for it. Dope atmosphere. Skate videos projected on the wall at high frame rate, which until you see it, you don't realize is the only way a skate video should be displayed. $3 Tecates. Solid venue for loading up before a night out.
Great fresh food and quick service with friendly staff and a great atmosphere
The food is good. The Guac is good but over priced. Order something that comes with guac like nachos and enjoy it that way.  Got the Al Pastor and it had a nice spicy flavor.
My favorite Mexican restaurant in NYC. Delicious cocktails, tasty bites, and a fun atmosphere.

Man this is good food! The nachos are incredible, your perfect late night snack - delicious, greasy (tho not actually greasy) pile of chips, guac, beans, cheese and in this case pork, but they have all the meats. The quesadilla and Mexican Corn were also on point.  The atmosphere was bumping. They had a DJ, mixing in hip hop and electronic. Very elaborate set up for an otherwise normal, counter service Mexican joint. They also have a full bar- with a huge list of Mezcal and tequila!!!  This place is fun! Perfect place to fall into before, during or after hitting the bars in Williamsburg!!!
Too slow but good food
The burrito is not the way to go here, fyi.
Delicious tacos  I had the chicken and the steak, I prefer the chicken but the steak was pretty good as well, safe to assume other items are just as delicious..

(Translated by Google) Good tacos, the establishment is cozy and has a nice look. Good service and good location. I recommend it for a beer , some tacos and some nachos.  (Original) Buenos tacos, el establecimiento es acogedor y tiene un look bonito. Buen servicio y buena ubicación. Lo recomiendo para tomarse una cerveza , unos tacos y unos nachos.
Solid Mexican food
I love this place... Salad is great!.. Buffalo wings are great!... Corn is great!... Quesadilla is different from others and really good!.. I come here all the time and definitely recommend it.
Good happy hour at the bar and a huge range of tequila and mezcals. Haven't tried the food yet, will go back soon and review my review :)

Great style. I loved the quesadilla, and the loaded fries. They need hotter hot sauce. Lol.  It was good we tried all the sauces. On the chicken nachos. Plenty  nachos for 6 lol the burritos are wrapped tight , the tacos are awesome i really liked the laid back style
Tasty tacos and good margs.
Good portion sizes, and so very tasty!
Excellent mexican food, clean restaurant, great service!
Not great food, overpriced everything.
Cool spot
Great vibe and place
I’ve been seeing this places on my way to work for a while and always wanted to stop. Today I did and didn’t disappoint food was great and love the environment.

(Translated by Google) The place is very nice and clean, even the bathrooms are very clean, you feel a very quiet atmosphere that invites you to enjoy your food, as far as the service is more or less, the food in the same way, I ordered two tacos al pastor and the meat was overcooked, I could even say it was crispy, my friend's burrito in the same way, prices a little above $.  (Original) El lugar es muy bonito y limpio, hasta los baños están muy limpios , se siente una atmósfera muy tranquila que te invita a disfrutar tu comida , en cuanto al servicio esta más  o menos , la comida de igual manera,  pedi dos tacos al pastor y la carne estaba sobrecocinada ,hasta podía decir que estaba crujiente,  el burrito de mi amigo de igual manera , los precios un poquito arriba de $ .

(Translated by Google) My husband went to buy two burritos around 11 pm .. the omelette It was so raw that we had to take out the stuffing and eat it like that .. which was A bit dry I had almost no cheese and zero cream. For what it costs each one that is $ 11 is not worth it!  (Original) Mi marido fue a comprar dos burritos alrededor de las 11 pm .. la tortilla Estaba tan cruda  que  tuvimos que sacarle el relleno y comerlo así .. el cual era Un poco seco no tenía casi nada de queso y cero crema . Para lo que cuesta cada uno que es $11 no lo vale !
Loved the Nachos and Elote. Staff was nice.

Food was excellent so were the drinks and the service. Well priced in fact a lot cheaper than I expected. Definitely recommend this place for either a quick nosh or a boozy sesh at the bar with some good food.

A good place to grab some drinks and eat some Mexican food. Food was good (not bad but not amazing). I ordered 3 tacos and chips. The nachos looked very good so I'd probably get those next time. Order at the counter and they bring the food out to you.
Food was good. Portions were small but flavor was good. Service was good. And drinks just need a little more liquor. But great atmosphere!
Not good. Everything is under seasoned and meat quality was poor.
Chicken wings are to die forrrrrrr.

Rice in the burrito was undercooked/crunchy, and the amount of steak was miniscule to the point of questioning whether or not it had been forgotten (especially for a markup). Thought Al pastor was dry though was almost saved with a squeeze of lime. Good tortilla, but the burrito was very disappointing...
Amazing tacos. My favorite was the Al Pastor.
Heard from a friend it's really good so gave it a try. Very impressed with the nachos and corn. Both well done. Will be back
Got the overstuffed fries. They we're pretty good. Quite filling.
If I could get a refund , I would've .. Rice was so hard! Ugh, such a disappointment!
Came here yesterday. Welcoming space with great decor. The food was fairly price. Got the nachos and it was enough for maybe three people or two hungry people.  Will come again,
Pretty good, great drinks

The chef on this place its someone whos kind and hes such a nice guy every time y say hi to him i end up having a fantastic conversation may take time away to make the food but its worth it cause when the food arrives I feel it took the time and love to be done the way i love it and if someone wold go in to that kitchen to salute mase chef Hamurabi he may be into some fish tacos but never too busy to give you the best see food in the whole sinaloa surroundings. Yet local products with international food procces. Why ask for more when the care and love thas in the food can take you to a new place home.
Open late! Great!
Best taqueria on the east coast. I've been to about 35 taquerias east of the Mississippi River... This is the only good one.
Best quesadilla I've had in a long time. Friendly staff and great location

Lunch was great here; I tried Grilled Shrimp and Chicken tacos. They we're both delicious. Also, I got the Corn which was also good. The service is extremely fast here like it took them 5min for my order and staff was very friendly.
Great vibe, good drinks

Get atmosphere but super slow service. Waited 35 mins for two tacos lmao. Yeah I used"lmao". The hostess tried to make it up by giving me a free soda. Tacos were just okay. Maybe I'll go for the burrito next time.
(Translated by Google) I ate a burrito at the recommendation I should have made tacos  (Original) オススメでブリトー食べた タコスにすればよかった
It took a really long time to get the food and food itself was a lot drier than the location I go to in the city
Good food
Love the atmosphere, food is great. Music is usually great. Not usually too packed. One of my favorite spots. Good for groups or a date.
Great tacos
(Translated by Google) Very good services  (Original) Muy buen servicios
The food is good, atmosphere was great but they are a bit overpriced that's why I gave 4 stars

Nice atmosphere on a weekday afternoon. Had a projector playing the world cup game. $6 margaritas at happy hour. Counter service was convenient and self-serve ice water was provided. Really enjoyed the carne asada fries-- big serving.
We went to Taqueria Diana because we were craving for tacos! They were DELICIOUS!! Thier shrimp tacos & chicken tacos were so food. Great flavor with some good heat!
Amazing Food
Cool place, but the food was pretty disappointing. @management, How about not putting the happy hour sign on the weekend when it's only M-F?

The new location is within stumbling distance of some of my favorite bars, and features the as usual excellent Mexican fare plus booze, in a larger than usual (for TD) restaurant. A welcome addition to the neighborhood.

I had high hopes for this place because it was on a Time Out NY "Top xx Burritos in NYC" list. In reality, the meat is dry, like almost jerky, and the rice is crunchy, like they just poured boiling water over it and called it a day. I'd rather regret my purchases at Chipotle.
Good little taco joint with a small outdoor area and tasty drinks
Get the al pastor
Very tasty nachos and burrito
The food here made me so sick the next day I had to go to the doctor. Turns out the chicken was undercooked because now I have salmonella food poisoning. Avoid at all costs.
There are dope late night tacos (and nachos) in Willliamsburg. Also draft Mikkeler.
Horrible food, dry rice and beans, really small portions.

I enjoyed very much my pollo plate I ordered to go. The food felt as if it needed more condiments though, in particular salt, but after a few bytes I started to enjoy it. I would have given five stars if the portion wasn’t so small. I was still hungry after I finished everything.

So I was in the area for a concert and pretty famished. My cousin and I just figured we’d give this place a try and wow we were impressed. My cousin had the steak tacos and I had the steak quesadilla and chicken quesadilla... DELICIOUS!!! The meat was well seasoned and prepared medium-well. Drinks are great too!! Definitely try the margaritas. The energy was good.. the playlist was West Coast old school hip-hop with a lil Biggie here or there. There’s a chill Cali dude that works there named Brett. He had the best energy, I just loved him!!! He was very attentive and super cool. It was definitely a great time. If you’re ever in  Williamsburg stop by, you won’t regret it!
Best tacos in Williamsburg.  Very clean, friendly and nice looking place.
